Gemini said



*Sort Smarter, Not Harder!*





To ensure every order is delivered by the most suitable network, we=E2=80=
=99re
introducing *Order Categories* =E2=80=94 enabling smarter routing, better
operational alignment, and improved delivery outcomes.


What=E2=80=99s New




*Order Categories Across Business & Network*
You can now define Order Categories at both:

   -

   *Business Level*
   -

      Parcel *(Default)*
      -

      Food
      -

   *Network Level*
   -

      Any *(Default =E2=80=93 category agnostic)*
      -

      Parcel
      -

      Food


*Smart Network Mapping*

   -

   Orders are now matched only with *eligible networks based on category*
   -

   Networks set to *=E2=80=9CAny=E2=80=9D* remain universally visible
   -

   Category-specific networks will only appear for matching orders




*Order Creation API Support*
Order category can now be passed directly during order creation via API
using:

   -

   *Key:* order_category
   -

   *Values:* parcel, food
   If not provided then the system falls back to Business defaults
   -


*Serviceability Control *Network visibility in the *serviceability modal* i=
s
   now governed by Order Category
   Only relevant networks are shown during order allocation
   Ensures *accurate routing and reduced operational errors*

What This Means To You




   -

   *Better Operational Alignment*
   -

      Food deliveries can be routed to networks optimized for *speed &
      perishability*
      -

      Parcel deliveries can be assigned to networks optimized for *cost &
      batching*


      -

   *Improved Delivery Accuracy*
   -

      Eliminates incorrect network selection during order creation
      -

      Reduces manual intervention and routing errors


      -

   *Standardized Workflow via API*
   -

      External systems can now directly control order categorization
      -

      Ensures seamless integration with SOPs and 3PL requirements


      View Documentation
      <https://documenter.getpostman.com/view/13758726/2s93RKzFtk#0aac3c63-=
e0d2-4e3f-9ac3-ca677ea8f6a8>



*Important Notes*

   1.

   If no category is configured anywhere, the system defaults to *Parcel.*
   2.

   Category selection directly impacts *network visibility and eligibility*


What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
